freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Chills most of last night and headache today.
Low grade fever and chills. Was COVID tested and it was negative. Went to urgent care and diagnosed with sinus infection. The Dr prescribed Augmentin and I was fine in less than 48 hours.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: I felt a sudden rush and then my blood pressure dropped to 90 over 50 and my pulse ox dropped to 93. But, feeling much better now. Blood pressure 115 over 70 and pulse ox 96
